WEBVTT

00:08.620 --> 00:10.689
[ birdsong ]

00:13.620 --> 00:16.620
[ music ]

01:41.482 --> 01:43.965
- Ride those east
pastures, Kayce.

01:44.034 --> 01:47.551
With all this rain, see if
any of that clover came up.

01:47.620 --> 01:49.034
- Yeah. It'll be easy to spot.

01:50.896 --> 01:53.551
You gonna be back
by tonight?

01:53.620 --> 01:57.206
- Doesn't... Doesn't take long
to quit something, son.

01:57.275 --> 01:58.586
I'll be back by noon.

02:00.793 --> 02:01.862
Let's go.

02:05.965 --> 02:08.241
Here. You'll dress
in the car.

02:22.655 --> 02:24.793
[ engine starts ]

02:35.379 --> 02:36.413
[ Tate screaming ]

02:37.482 --> 02:39.206
- Hey. Hey. Tate. Tate.

02:39.275 --> 02:40.758
Look at me.

02:40.827 --> 02:43.758
Tate, Tate, stop.
It's okay, it's okay.

02:43.827 --> 02:44.758
Stop.

02:44.827 --> 02:46.068
- Don't say it.

02:46.137 --> 02:48.827
- I don't have to.

02:48.896 --> 02:51.275
I can't say it any
better than that.

02:52.344 --> 02:53.310
- It's okay.

02:54.827 --> 02:57.517
Just... Just
go back to sleep, son, okay?

03:12.758 --> 03:16.827
[ music ]

04:20.586 --> 04:22.689
- Exactly as I told you
to say it, understood?

04:22.758 --> 04:24.482
- Understood.
Trust me.

04:29.344 --> 04:30.482
- Trust me?

04:33.896 --> 04:35.586
[ scoffs ]

04:39.310 --> 04:40.275
- He's gonna walk in here--
- [ knocking ]

04:40.344 --> 04:41.655
- Okay, no.
[ door opens ]

04:41.724 --> 04:43.413
- Hello, John.

04:43.482 --> 04:44.482
- Lynelle.

04:47.344 --> 04:49.241
- I, uh... I don't know
where to start.

04:52.896 --> 04:54.137
- I know where to start.

04:56.000 --> 04:58.137
- We had evidence that
the Becks used aircraft

04:58.206 --> 05:00.620
to poison cattle
along the highway 89 corridor

05:00.689 --> 05:02.137
south of Emigrant.

05:02.206 --> 05:03.931
Upon serving a warrant based
on that information,

05:04.000 --> 05:06.137
we discovered additional
evidence of a kidnapping--

05:06.206 --> 05:07.931
- We know all this, Jamie.

05:08.000 --> 05:09.517
- Livestock agents
are bound by law

05:09.586 --> 05:11.551
to intervene in
any active crime.

05:11.620 --> 05:14.689
That duty supersedes
jurisdictional boundaries.

05:16.310 --> 05:18.655
- You gonna fight this, John?

05:18.724 --> 05:20.344
- Are we wrong?

05:20.413 --> 05:23.068
- You're not wrong.
But it doesn't alter the lens.

05:23.137 --> 05:26.275
It doesn't change the way
it looks and how it looks--

05:26.344 --> 05:29.379
- Is all that matters
anymore, John.

05:29.448 --> 05:30.862
Six people died.

05:32.275 --> 05:34.000
The door is closed, John.

05:34.068 --> 05:35.551
Let's just be honest.

05:35.620 --> 05:37.896
When the blanket gets pulled
back on this thing,

05:37.965 --> 05:39.551
and the nation knows
that the family member

05:39.620 --> 05:41.827
that was kidnapped was yours...

05:41.896 --> 05:43.586
This stops looking
like law enforcement

05:43.655 --> 05:45.655
and starts looking like...
- It looks like a feud.

05:45.724 --> 05:48.241
It looks like
a gross misuse of power.

05:48.310 --> 05:50.344
Lynelle: We have been sitting
here banging our heads

05:50.413 --> 05:53.551
against a wall,
and we don't have a solution.

05:53.620 --> 05:55.103
- I have a solution, Lynelle.

05:57.862 --> 05:59.689
You leave the blanket
right where it is.

06:02.586 --> 06:04.344
I'll resign as
Livestock Commissioner

06:04.413 --> 06:08.172
and accept full responsibility
for my agents' overreach.

06:08.241 --> 06:11.758
And you, you stop looking.

06:13.172 --> 06:15.068
You let it go.

06:15.137 --> 06:17.896
You talk about militias
and human smuggling

06:17.965 --> 06:19.448
and you take the credit.

06:19.517 --> 06:23.379
And you leave me
and my family out of it.

06:31.275 --> 06:34.034
- That cleans things up
on my end.

06:34.103 --> 06:36.965
- This is a state issue and
that's where I want it to stay.

06:37.034 --> 06:38.793
- And this keeps
it a state issue?

06:38.862 --> 06:40.413
- It gives me
what I need, yes.

06:43.724 --> 06:44.862
- Great.

06:45.931 --> 06:47.620
Have you thought
about your replacement?

06:50.172 --> 06:51.862
- Give me till next week.

06:54.965 --> 06:56.896
- Thank you, John.

06:56.965 --> 06:59.068
I won't forget this.

06:59.137 --> 07:00.758
- I won't let you.

07:00.827 --> 07:01.827
- I'm sure you won't.

07:11.758 --> 07:13.965
- There was a closed door
meeting with the Governor,

07:14.034 --> 07:16.034
the Attorney General,
Federal Officials,

07:16.103 --> 07:18.068
and Livestock Commissioner
John Dutton.

07:18.137 --> 07:20.724
Now, Dutton's office
is under intense scrutiny

07:20.793 --> 07:23.206
for its use of force
in multiple gun battles

07:23.275 --> 07:24.551
that led to the death
of both Beck brothers...

07:24.620 --> 07:28.275
- How do you think
this is gonna work out for him?

07:28.344 --> 07:32.379
- Depends, on whether he's
as smart as I think he is.

07:32.448 --> 07:33.965
- I watched him.

07:34.034 --> 07:36.448
In a field.

07:36.517 --> 07:38.172
He had honor
when most wouldn't.

07:40.517 --> 07:42.862
- What are you saying?

07:42.931 --> 07:45.448
- I'm saying, maybe he's
not the enemy we think he is.

07:48.620 --> 07:51.103
- When there's
one thing that two men want,

07:51.172 --> 07:54.586
they can either share it
or be enemies.

07:54.655 --> 07:57.034
Are you suggesting we share it?

07:57.103 --> 08:00.137
- Suggesting things
isn't my job, Chairman.

08:00.206 --> 08:01.689
That's yours.

08:23.965 --> 08:25.965
- This side looks good.

08:26.034 --> 08:27.206
- This side too.

08:28.862 --> 08:32.000
- You feel good turning
cattle back out?

08:32.068 --> 08:34.862
- It should have clovered up
this last rain.

08:34.931 --> 08:37.344
I think we ought
to wait until July.

08:37.413 --> 08:39.965
- We're running out of hay.

08:40.034 --> 08:43.034
Feeding cattle all summer is
no way to make a living.

08:43.103 --> 08:45.275
- Shit, we'll just do it
like the old days:

08:45.344 --> 08:46.758
grab a chuck wagon,
bring it out here

08:46.827 --> 08:48.862
and we'll babysit 'em
all summer long.

08:48.931 --> 08:50.827
- It's not the worst idea.

08:50.896 --> 08:52.034
The fuck?

08:57.896 --> 08:59.000
- Who the fuck are they?

09:10.344 --> 09:11.586
- Y'all lost?

09:11.655 --> 09:14.206
- Uh, it's a possibility.

09:14.275 --> 09:17.482
Uh, is this part of the
Paradise Valley Sporting Club?

09:17.551 --> 09:19.758
- Wrong side of that fence.

09:19.827 --> 09:21.586
- Ah. I told you.
[ chuckles ]

09:22.827 --> 09:24.827
- You all staying at
the Sporting Club?

09:24.896 --> 09:26.862
- Uh, they own it.

09:26.931 --> 09:28.034
- Who are they?

09:28.103 --> 09:30.103
- Providence Hospitality
management.

09:30.172 --> 09:32.275
I'm Ellis Steele.

09:32.344 --> 09:34.482
my firm is representing
Market Equities.

09:38.137 --> 09:39.724
- We don't know what that is.

09:39.793 --> 09:41.758
- They manage resort properties.

09:41.827 --> 09:43.137
We watch out for
their interests.

09:44.413 --> 09:46.413
This your land?

09:46.482 --> 09:49.000
Incredible.

09:49.068 --> 09:51.482
I didn't catch your name?

09:51.551 --> 09:53.137
- That's cause I didn't
offer it.

09:58.896 --> 10:00.103
- Fair enough.

10:01.586 --> 10:02.586
We'll get out of your way.

10:05.758 --> 10:07.413
You know, I can understand
you being wary,

10:07.482 --> 10:09.827
bunch of city folks
wandering in your field.

10:09.896 --> 10:11.758
I apologize.

10:11.827 --> 10:14.689
Why don't you come by the resort
and have dinner, on us?

10:14.758 --> 10:16.310
After all, you're going
to be neighbors,

10:16.379 --> 10:18.000
it's best
if we all get along.

10:22.551 --> 10:24.034
[ chuckles ]

10:31.310 --> 10:32.482
We're going this way, folks.

10:40.827 --> 10:42.689
- The properties
highlighted in red

10:42.758 --> 10:45.206
are the ones we've purchased.

10:45.275 --> 10:47.172
- How much acreage total?

10:47.241 --> 10:49.137
- A little over 17,000.

10:49.206 --> 10:51.448
- [ chuckles ]
Ooh, damn.

10:51.517 --> 10:52.931
Good job, Beth.

10:53.000 --> 10:54.689
- It's what you pay me to do.

10:54.758 --> 10:56.103
- Any of it commercially zoned?

10:56.172 --> 10:58.137
- Most of the highway
frontage is multi-use.

10:58.206 --> 11:00.413
But the corner properties,
they're commercial.

11:00.482 --> 11:02.034
Why, what you thinking?

11:02.103 --> 11:04.413
- I want you to hold off on
the conservation easements.

11:04.482 --> 11:06.310
- That income offsets
our tax liability.

11:06.379 --> 11:09.000
- I know, but there could be
bigger income on the horizon.

11:09.068 --> 11:11.241
Market Equities bought
Jenkins' place.

11:11.310 --> 11:13.310
Hired a hotel management
group to oversee it.

11:13.379 --> 11:14.551
- That was fast.

11:14.620 --> 11:15.862
- The estate didn't
have a choice.

11:15.931 --> 11:17.655
He was losing
six figures a month.

11:17.724 --> 11:20.275
Bank was going to call the note.

11:20.344 --> 11:23.758
- So, who is running
the property now?

11:23.827 --> 11:25.206
- Providence.

11:27.758 --> 11:29.413
- That's a big company.

11:29.482 --> 11:32.103
- It's the one you bring in
when your goal is expansion.

11:32.172 --> 11:35.172
And your expansion is bigger
than casinos and golf courses.

11:37.413 --> 11:39.344
- You heard any rumors
about their plans?

11:39.413 --> 11:42.965
- Probably the same as their
plans in Austin and Scottsdale.

11:43.034 --> 11:46.310
Beth, keep buying.

11:46.379 --> 11:48.655
But every fucking thing you
can get your hands on.

11:48.724 --> 11:49.758
- Will do.

11:50.758 --> 11:53.724
[ country music plays ]

11:53.793 --> 11:55.344
[ construction sounds ]

11:57.310 --> 11:59.862
- What's wrong with
the old barn?

11:59.931 --> 12:03.793
- It's seven miles from
this half of the ranch.

12:03.862 --> 12:05.517
- Hey, Lloyd, what, uh...

12:05.586 --> 12:07.896
What was that old joke
about the two fat chicks

12:07.965 --> 12:09.931
and the wheelbarrows?
[ laughs ]

12:10.000 --> 12:12.517
- That wasn't a joke, Jake.

12:12.586 --> 12:14.793
That was you at
the Cooper branding.

12:14.862 --> 12:16.793
- You guys wanna hear a joke?

12:16.862 --> 12:17.965
[All]
- No.

12:18.034 --> 12:19.137
- All right, check it out.

12:19.206 --> 12:20.517
There's this big
Texas oil guy, right?

12:20.586 --> 12:22.724
Goes into this bar down
at the border,

12:22.793 --> 12:23.862
sits next to this
vaquero and says,

12:23.931 --> 12:25.827
"Hey, man, you a rancher?"

12:25.896 --> 12:29.206
Vaquero says, "Yeah, I got
fifty acres down by the river."

12:29.275 --> 12:32.137
Big Texas oil guy says,
"Oh? Oh, on my ranch,

12:32.206 --> 12:34.344
"I can get in my truck
in the morning,

12:34.413 --> 12:37.068
and I still don't reach
the front gate by sunset."

12:37.137 --> 12:39.310
Vaquero sits for a second,
nods, and says,

12:39.379 --> 12:42.344
"Yeah, man. Yeah, I used to have
a truck like that too."

12:47.793 --> 12:49.482
I...

12:49.551 --> 12:51.103
He was bragging about
the size of his ranch,

12:51.172 --> 12:52.551
and the vaquero...
- That was almost funny.

12:52.620 --> 12:53.931
- All right, I got one.

12:54.000 --> 12:55.551
Y'all hear about the guy
that goes to see a doctor,

12:55.620 --> 12:58.379
and the doctor says, "Sorry to
be the one to tell you this,

12:58.448 --> 13:00.103
"but you got cancer head to toe.

13:00.172 --> 13:02.379
Only have one week to live."

13:02.448 --> 13:03.862
Man says, "A week?!
Well, that's not enough time!

13:03.931 --> 13:05.241
"Doc, you gotta do something.

13:05.310 --> 13:06.517
I need more than a week!"

13:06.586 --> 13:09.620
And the Doc thinks, he sits down
and he says,

13:09.689 --> 13:10.931
"I'll tell you what to do:

13:11.000 --> 13:13.241
"you go find yourself
a barrel racer girl

13:13.310 --> 13:18.172
with two little dogs,
and you marry her."

13:18.241 --> 13:20.103
And the man says, "That's gonna
make me live longer?"

13:20.172 --> 13:21.551
And the Doc says, "No.

13:21.620 --> 13:24.103
But it'll make that week
feel like a fucking eternity."

13:24.172 --> 13:25.275
[ laughing ]

13:27.931 --> 13:29.586
- I don't know.
I think mine was better.

13:29.655 --> 13:31.310
- Jimmy, when you're
all growed up,

13:31.379 --> 13:33.103
and you've actually
dated a woman,

13:33.172 --> 13:34.724
you'll think it's hilarious.

13:34.793 --> 13:37.344
- That's it.
Let's go up to the big barn.

13:37.413 --> 13:41.068
You're done.
Let's go.

13:41.137 --> 13:44.482
Lloyd, let's get them
mules out of the field.

13:44.551 --> 13:46.103
Let's clean up
that chuck wagon.

13:46.172 --> 13:48.620
We're running a spike camp
this summer, understand?

13:50.379 --> 13:52.724
- Ethan, come on.

13:52.793 --> 13:54.586
- Wait, what's a spike camp?

13:55.655 --> 13:57.896
[ music playing ]

14:07.241 --> 14:08.862
- It's 38 even.

14:12.517 --> 14:14.655
Care to donate to the jar fund?

14:14.724 --> 14:15.724
- Sure.

14:17.827 --> 14:19.000
Oh, I'm good.

14:20.655 --> 14:23.068
You know, you should start
a "GoFundMe" page.

14:23.137 --> 14:24.758
- What's that?

14:24.827 --> 14:25.793
- It's, um...

14:27.206 --> 14:29.379
It's a pickle jar
the whole world can reach.

14:32.172 --> 14:33.482
Your boy?

14:39.448 --> 14:40.482
Dealing with this

14:40.551 --> 14:42.068
and he still
does that to you?

14:45.655 --> 14:48.103
- Someone's doing it
to you, too.

14:48.172 --> 14:49.793
- Not anymore they're not.

14:52.344 --> 14:53.551
- How...

14:56.344 --> 14:57.931
How did you make him stop?

15:01.413 --> 15:03.931
- My boyfriend put
his head through a wall,

15:04.000 --> 15:06.586
then I smashed his skull
with an eight pound ashtray.

15:08.206 --> 15:10.758
New boyfriend.

15:10.827 --> 15:12.137
Big-ass ashtray.

15:14.931 --> 15:16.517
It's just a thought...

15:24.379 --> 15:25.586
[ phone rings ]

15:28.275 --> 15:29.551
- Hey.

15:29.620 --> 15:31.241
Kayce: What's Providence
Hospitality?

15:33.448 --> 15:35.241
- It's a problem.

15:35.310 --> 15:37.103
- How big?

15:37.172 --> 15:39.000
- They don't get any bigger.

15:42.965 --> 15:44.379
Listen, don't tell Dad.
Okay?

15:44.448 --> 15:47.689
I gotta go, some asshole's
standing in our river.

15:52.241 --> 15:53.448
- Hey.

15:55.310 --> 15:56.310
Hey!

15:58.103 --> 16:00.517
- How ya doing?

16:00.586 --> 16:03.068
- You're trespassing!

16:03.137 --> 16:05.137
- Huh?

16:05.206 --> 16:06.965
- Trespassing!

16:08.034 --> 16:09.862
- What?

16:09.931 --> 16:11.896
- Get out of our
fucking river.

16:13.517 --> 16:15.689
- I can't
That would be trespassing.

16:17.620 --> 16:19.103
- This fucking guy...

16:34.793 --> 16:36.172
- I see the women in this valley

16:36.241 --> 16:38.103
have gotten a
lot more fashionable.

16:38.172 --> 16:39.689
- Yeah?

16:39.758 --> 16:42.724
I see Chippendale's changed
their policy on capped teeth.

16:43.793 --> 16:44.896
- What's that?

16:44.965 --> 16:46.413
- It's an insult.

16:46.482 --> 16:48.068
Never mind.

16:48.137 --> 16:49.551
- Only an insult
if I understand it.

16:49.620 --> 16:51.344
- Yeah, that's not true.

16:51.413 --> 16:53.137
But that's a conversation
for another time.

16:53.206 --> 16:54.724
That we'll never have.

16:54.793 --> 16:57.620
Both sides of the river
are private property.

16:57.689 --> 16:59.655
- I know.
That's why I can't get out.

16:59.724 --> 17:02.241
- Well, how did you get in?

17:02.310 --> 17:03.620
- My family owns
a place upriver.

17:03.689 --> 17:05.689
Cross Creek Ranch.
You know it?

17:05.758 --> 17:07.689
- Yeah, that's
five miles upstream.

17:07.758 --> 17:09.551
- I was blessed with stamina.

17:09.620 --> 17:11.482
- I highly doubt it.

17:11.551 --> 17:15.310
- When I played golf,
I'd do 36 holes in a day.

17:15.379 --> 17:16.862
I like this much better.

17:16.931 --> 17:19.620
It's just like golf,
but with fish.

17:21.689 --> 17:23.172
You have any interest in dinner?

17:23.241 --> 17:24.413
- No.

17:24.482 --> 17:26.344
- I meant in general.

17:26.413 --> 17:29.758
- No.
I dine on my joy for life.

17:29.827 --> 17:30.896
- Ah.

17:30.965 --> 17:33.275
- Just stay off
our fucking land, okay?

17:33.344 --> 17:36.103
- Yes, ma'am.

17:36.172 --> 17:37.379
I'll stay off
your fucking land.

17:37.448 --> 17:38.758
I promise.

17:39.758 --> 17:41.517
Thanks for the talk!

17:41.586 --> 17:43.034
You're the most
interesting thing

17:43.103 --> 17:45.068
that's happened to me today.

17:45.137 --> 17:47.620
- You should analyze that.

17:47.689 --> 17:49.206
- [ chuckles ]

18:06.310 --> 18:08.758
- How'd it go?

18:08.827 --> 18:11.724
- Like I expected.

18:11.793 --> 18:13.241
It's a good trade for them.

18:13.310 --> 18:15.034
They were happy to make it.

18:15.103 --> 18:18.034
- How bout you?
You happy?

18:20.241 --> 18:22.551
- I never wanted
that office, Beth.

18:22.620 --> 18:25.793
I just...
wanted the control.

18:27.827 --> 18:28.931
I still have that.

18:30.551 --> 18:32.827
- This might be
a tougher sell.

18:32.896 --> 18:35.068
- Well, lucky I got you
to sell it for me.

18:43.655 --> 18:44.862
- How are the fields?

18:46.275 --> 18:48.689
- They're green.

18:48.758 --> 18:50.482
- No clover?

18:50.551 --> 18:53.620
- None that I could see.
Grass is tall, though.

18:53.689 --> 18:55.000
I was thinking we should
run a camp up there

18:55.068 --> 18:56.551
and keep an eye on 'em.

18:56.620 --> 18:58.448
Oh, and there's something going
down at Paradise Valley.

18:58.517 --> 19:00.655
There's a bunch of suits
wandering around up there
when we got up there.

19:02.655 --> 19:03.896
- Suits?

19:03.965 --> 19:05.482
- Yeah, I was gonna get to that.

19:07.103 --> 19:09.344
- Well, one problem at a time.

19:11.965 --> 19:14.689
I need to name
my replacement as Commissioner.

19:17.344 --> 19:18.689
I'm naming you.

19:24.344 --> 19:25.931
- You mean you're just gonna
tell me this now?

19:26.000 --> 19:27.689
After you already quit?

19:27.758 --> 19:31.896
- If I told you before,
you'd say no.

19:31.965 --> 19:34.137
Then I couldn't quit.
- Well, I'm still saying no.

19:34.206 --> 19:35.551
- Kayce--

19:35.620 --> 19:37.068
- I ain't no politician!

19:37.137 --> 19:38.310
You want a politician?

19:38.379 --> 19:39.827
You've got one standing
right there.

19:39.896 --> 19:41.068
You got another one
in the bunkhouse

19:41.137 --> 19:42.931
living like a fucking orphan.
- Kayce--

19:43.000 --> 19:45.103
- I told you I would
help you run this place,

19:45.172 --> 19:48.689
and I'm doing that
the only way I know how.

19:48.758 --> 19:49.931
I won't do it.

19:55.689 --> 19:57.620
- Can I make a suggestion?

19:57.689 --> 19:59.551
- Yeah, as long as it's you.

20:00.551 --> 20:02.655
- Can't be me.

20:02.724 --> 20:05.000
- I need family
